X,Y,Z
(3,0,1)
 \frac {X+1}4 = \frac {Y-2}{-2} = \frac {Z+6}7 = k \\ X = 4k - 1 \\ Y = -2k + 2 \\ Z = 7k - 6 
 3X+8Y-9Z = 0 \\ 12k-3 - 16k + 16 - 63k + 54 = 0 \\ -67k + 67 = 0 \\ k = 1 
 X = 4k-1 = 3 \\ Y = -2k+2 = 0 \\ Z = 7k-6 = 1 
y=\frac{-x-1}2+2=\frac{-x+3}2\;,\;\;z=\frac{7x+7}4-6=\frac{7x-17}{4}
3x+8\left(\frac{-x+3}2\right)-9\left(\frac{7x-17}4\right)=0\iff -\frac{67}4x+\frac{201}4=0\implies
 x=3\;,\;y=0\;,\;z=1
